om, H.B., Sommer, S.G., (2001) Kvælstof, fosfor og kalium i husdyrgødning - normtal 2000 (Standard values of nitrogen, phosphorous and potassium in animal manure), p. 152. , DJF-Report - Husdyrgødning nr. 36, Miljøministeriet for fødevarer, landbrug og fiskeri. Danmarks Jordbrugsforskning, Tjele; (2002) Tecniche di riduzione delle emis-sioni in atmosfera originate dagli allevamenti zootecnici (Emission reduction techniques from livestock production), , Regione Emilia-Romagna Internal report, edited by C.R.P.A; (2004) Le Migliori Tecniche Disponibili per la riduzione delle emissioni dalle attività di allevamento (Best available techniques for the reduction of the emissions from livestock production), , Regione Emilia-Romagna Internal report, edited by C.R.P.A; Rochette, P., Janzen, H.H., Towards a revised coefficient for estimating N2O emissions from legumes (2005) Nutrient Cycling in Agroecosystems, 73, pp. 171-179; Saffih-Hdadi, K., Mary, B., Modeling consequences of straw residues export on soil organic carbon (2008) Soil Biology and Bio-chemistry, 40, pp. 594-607; Schils, R.L.M., Olesen, J.E., del Prado, A., Soussana, J.F., A review of farm level modelling approaches for mitigating greenhouse gas emissions from ruminant livestock systems (2007) Livestock Science, 112, pp. 240-251; Schils, R.L.M., Verhagen, A., Aarts, H.F.M., Kuikman, P.J., Šebek, L.B.J., Effect of improved nitrogen management on green-house gas emissions from intensive dairy systems in the Netherlands (2006) Global Change Biology, 12, pp. 382-391; Sherlock, R.R., Sommer, S.G., Rehmat, Z., Emission of ammonia, methane and nitrous oxide from pig slurry applied to a pasture in New Zealand (2002) Journal of Environmental Quality, 31, pp. 1491-1501; Sleutel, S., De Neve, S., Hofman, G., Assessing causes of recent organic carbon losses from cropland soils by means of regio-nal-scaled input balances for the case of Flanders (Belgium) (2007) Nutrient Cycling in Agroecosystems, 78, pp. 265-278; Smith, P.,